programme.desc: A profile of the former boxer, a four-time world super-middleweight champion considered among the elite performers in his weight class. After rising through the domestic ranks and winning both the British and Commonwealth titles, Froch claimed his first world crown by defeating Jean Pascal in 2008, and was a dominant fighter on the world scene from that point on. His legacy was assured in May 2014 when he defeated fellow Brit George Groves in a rematch at Wembley Stadium in what proved to be his final fight. That contest drew what was then the largest attendance for a boxing bout in the UK since the Second World War at 80,000.(n)
